	<p class="blog-hero"><img src="/blog/images/super-simple-note-taking-notes.jpg"></p>

	<h2><a href="/blog/super-simple-note-taking-notes" class="permalink"
			  >New: super simple note taking with Notes</a></h2>

	<div class="blog-subheading">Quickly jot down your ideas, goals, and any other textual tidbits for later review.</div>

	<div class="blog-article-body">
		<p>We’re excited to announce our latest addition to Momentum, Notes! Notes is a super simple way to jot down notes right from within Momentum. Notes is also a place to keep quotes and longer passages of text close at hand, so you can keep coming back to them.</p>

<p>Your notes automatically save when you create and edit them. Once enabled, the Notes widget can be found near the bottom right corner of your dashboard — right next to the Todo widget. Create, edit, and store multiple notes at a time, and access them from any computer by logging in with your account.</p>


<h4>To get started using Notes:</h4>

<ol>
	<li>Click <strong><i class="fa fa-cog"></i> Settings</strong>.</li>
	<li>Find <strong>Notes</strong> under Widgets and </strong>click to enable</strong> it.</li>
	<li>The Notes widget will appear in the bottom right similar to Todo. Click and enjoy!</li>
</ol>


<h4>Keyboard Navigation</h4>

<p>We built keyboard navigation into our new Notes widget for quicker usage. Use <span class="hotkey">N</span> to open Notes (Momentum must be selected by clicking into Momentum or pressing <span>Tab</span> twice from the omnibar). To jump right into a New Note, press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + N</span>.</p>

<p>Navigate between notes in the list with the <span class="hotkey">↑</span> and <span class="hotkey">↓</span> keys. Press <span class="hotkey">Enter</span> to go into a note, and <span class="hotkey">Esc</span> for back.</p>

<p>For a more comprehensive look at Momentum’s hotkeys, check out our <a href="https://get.momentumdash.help/hc/en-us/articles/360012256874-Hotkeys-Keyboard-shortcuts" target="_blank">Hotkeys/Keyboard shortcut guide</a> in Momentum’s <a href="https://get.momentumdash.help/hc/en-us" target="_blank">Help Center</a>.</p>


<h4>Offline Sync</h4>

<p>Debuting also in the Notes widget is our new offline sync functionality. You can now working with your notes offline and when you get back online they will sync with your account.</p>


<h4>Next Up</h4>

<p>Next up for Notes is search filter to more quickly find notes as more get added.</p>


<h4>Using Notes like a Pro</h4>

<p>For more info on using the new Notes widget, check out our <a href="https://get.momentumdash.help/hc/en-us/articles/360012372293-Notes" target="_blank">Notes guide</a> in Momentum’s <a href="https://get.momentumdash.help/hc/en-us" target="_blank">Help Center</a>.</p>


<h4>Available on Plus</h4>

<p>Momentum Plus subscribers are currently receiving exclusive access to this widget, so if you are interested in using Notes please show us your support and <a href="/plus">subscribe</a>! Each subscription directly contributes to Momentum’s future development, which enables <a href="/about">us</a> to work on new additions like Notes, and also funds bigger projects like expanding to other browsers and creating a mobile app.</p>

As always, we love to hear your feedback on Notes at <a href="mailto:help@momentumdash.com">help@momentumdash.com</a>
	</div>

	<p class="blog-author">
		<img src="/img/team/bio-team.jpg" class="author-pic">The Momentum Team<span class="separator">&mdash;</span>January 9, 2017	</p>
</section>

